Help Type: topic
Topic: ai

AI Agent Contract

Primary contract:
  Use Wiki Graph URIs as stable object handles.
  When you have a URI and need valid operations, read `wikigraph help object`.
  When you know an operation and need valid targets, read `wikigraph help verb`.

Object command inputs:
  Never pass a bare filesystem path to URI-targeted commands.
  Convert archive paths into Wiki Graph URIs first:
    /Users/me/book.wikg -> wikg:///Users/me/book.wikg
    ./book.wikg -> wikg://book.wikg

Treat every search result as a Wiki Graph URI.
Search results may use short object URIs such as `wikg://entity/Q8018`; prepend the archive locator before passing them back to object commands:
  wikg:///absolute/path/book.wikg/entity/Q8018

Default exploration loop:
  1. `wikigraph help uri`
  2. `wikigraph help object`
  3. `wikigraph wikg:///absolute/path/book.wikg search <query>`
  4. `wikigraph <located-object-uri> get`
  5. `wikigraph <located-object-uri> related`
  6. `wikigraph <located-object-uri> evidence`
  7. Pick a located chunk or entity URI before `wikigraph <located-graph-object-uri> pack --budget <chars>`

Archive and job commands also use URI targets:
  wikigraph wikg://book.wikg create ./book.md
  wikigraph wikg://book.wikg/chapter list
  wikigraph wikg://local/job add --input wikg://book.wikg/chapter/3 --task reading-graph --accept-cost
  wikigraph wikg://local/job list
  wikigraph wikg://local/job/<job-id> watch --jsonl

Example:
  wikigraph wikg:///Users/me/book.wikg/entity search "朱元璋"

Use URI lenses to select searchable object kinds:
  wikg://book.wikg/chapter
  wikg://book.wikg/source
  wikg://book.wikg/summary
  wikg://book.wikg/chunk
  wikg://book.wikg/entity
  wikg://book.wikg/triple
  wikg://book.wikg/chapter/3/entity

Lens position controls scope: use `<archive-uri>/entity list` for an archive-wide entity inventory, and use `<chapter-uri>/entity list` only for one chapter.

When a user asks for source passages mentioning, grounding, or supporting a known entity, start from the entity URI:
  wikigraph <archive-uri>/entity/<qid> evidence

Do not use source search by the entity label as the primary method. Entity labels may have aliases, translations, variants, and grounded mentions that do not match the label text. Use source search only as a secondary literal-text check.

When investigating a known entity, chunk, or triple under a specific aspect, consider passing the aspect as the optional query to `evidence` or `related` first. This uses the current FTS index to filter and rank candidates while keeping the current object anchor.
  wikigraph <archive-uri>/entity/Q830077 evidence "objectivity"
  wikigraph <archive-uri>/entity/Q830077 related "objectivity" --evidence 2

Use `list` when recall or completeness matters more than narrowing. Read `wikigraph help retrieval` before choosing pagination or output format flags.

When investigating an entity:
  1. `wikigraph <archive-uri>/entity/<qid> get`
  2. `wikigraph <archive-uri>/entity/<qid> evidence`
  3. `wikigraph <archive-uri>/entity/<qid> related --evidence <n>`
  4. `wikigraph <archive-uri>/entity/<qid>/wikipage get`
  5. Use external web search only if the mapped wikipage is missing or insufficient.

Do not infer Wikipedia URLs from entity labels or Wikidata QIDs. Use `/entity/<qid>/wikipage get` to retrieve canonical mapped pages.

Retrieval strategy:
  Read `wikigraph help retrieval` for scope, lens, pagination, `--limit`, `--all`, `--json`, and `--jsonl` choices.

Source search hits and evidence previews include nearby source context by default. Use `--context 0` when the user needs exact cited ranges, and adjust `--context <n>` instead of switching to full source output when a small window is enough.
